The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Berlin: Roger Federer suffered a shock defeat by Lleyton Hewitt in the final of the Halle grasscourt event on Sunday, losing 3-6 7-6 6-4 to the Australian. It is only the second defeat for Federer in last 78 grass court appearances.        
	Eastbourne: Sania Mirza demolished the challenge of Jocelyn Rae 6-1, 6-2 to progress to the third and final qualifying round of the WTA Aegon International tournament.        
	Estoril: Gaganjeet Bhullar rode on a flawless back-nine to card a two-under 70 and rise to tied 47th after the third round of the Portugal Open here. Gaganjeet has a three-day total of three-under 213.        
	Calcutta: Mahendra Singh Dhoni and his India side can regain their top slots in the ICC ODI Player and Team Rankings list with a few good performances in the upcoming Asia Cup, according to a media release.    
	Team Rankings: 1. Australia 133; 2. South Africa 119; 3. India 118; 4. New Zealand 114; 5. England 110; 6. Sri Lanka 107; 7. Pakistan 104; 8. West Indies 71; 9. Bangladesh 52; 10. Zimbabwe 34; 11. Ireland 24; 12. Kenya 2        
	Chennai: Eight members of a 15-strong Indian team, including captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni, on Sunday left for Colombo to participate in the Asia Cup starting June 15.        
	London: The inventors of the much-criticised and often baffling Duckworth/Lewis system for deciding weather-hit cricket matches are all set to be honoured with MBEs by the Queen of England.                                                                                                                                                        
